attributes.name: filterMode
attributes.description:
Controls how the results of `customFilter` and `customKeyFilter` are combined. All modes only apply `customFilter` to columns not specified in `customKeyFilter`.

- **some**: There is at least one match from either the custom filter or the custom key filter.
- **every**: All columns match either the custom filter or the custom key filter.
- **union**: There is at least one match from the custom filter, or all columns match the custom key filters.
- **intersection**: There is at least one match from the custom filter, and all columns match the custom key filters.

attributes.name: noFilter
attributes.description: Do not apply filtering when searching. Useful when data is being filtered server side.

attributes.name: customFilter
attributes.description: Function used to filter items, called for each filterable key on each item in the list. The first argument is the filterable value from the item, the second is the search term, and the third is the internal item object. The function should return true if the item should be included in the filtered list, or the index of the match in the value if it should be included with the result highlighted.

attributes.name: activator
attributes.description: Explicitly sets the overlay's activator.

attributes.name: inset
attributes.description: Reduces the sheet content maximum width to 70%.

attributes.name: fullscreen
attributes.description: Changes layout for fullscreen display.

attributes.name: scrollable
attributes.description: When set to true, expects a `v-card` and a `v-card-text` component with a designated height. For more information, check out the [scrollable example](/components/dialogs#scrollable).

attributes.name: closeOnBack
attributes.description: Closes the overlay content when the browser's back button is pressed or `$router.back()` is called, cancelling the original navigation. `persistent` overlays will cancel navigation and animate as if they were clicked outside instead of closing.

attributes.name: contained
attributes.description: Limits the size of the component and scrim to its offset parent. Implies `absolute` and `attach`. (Note: The parent element must have position: relative.).

attributes.name: contentClass
attributes.description: Applies a custom class to the detached element. This is useful because the content is moved to the beginning of the `v-app` component (unless the **attach** prop is provided) and is not targetable by classes passed directly on the component.

attributes.name: contentProps
attributes.description: Apply custom properties to the content.

attributes.name: opacity
attributes.description: Sets the opacity of the scrim element. Only applies if `scrim` is enabled.

attributes.name: noClickAnimation
attributes.description: Disables the bounce effect when clicking outside of the content element when using the persistent prop.

attributes.name: persistent
attributes.description: Clicking outside of the element or pressing esc key will not deactivate it.

attributes.name: scrim
attributes.description: Accepts true/false to enable background, and string to define color.

attributes.name: zIndex
attributes.description: The z-index used for the component.

attributes.name: target
attributes.description: For locationStrategy="connected", specify an element or array of x,y coordinates that the overlay should position itself relative to. This will be the activator element by default.

attributes.name: activatorProps
attributes.description: Apply custom properties to the activator.

attributes.name: openOnClick
attributes.description: Activate the component when the activator is clicked.

attributes.name: openOnHover
attributes.description: Activate the component when the activator is hovered.

attributes.name: openOnFocus
attributes.description: Activate the component when the activator is focused.

attributes.name: closeOnContentClick
attributes.description: Closes component when you click on its content.

attributes.name: closeDelay
attributes.description: Milliseconds to wait before closing component. Only applies to hover and focus events.

attributes.name: openDelay
attributes.description: Milliseconds to wait before opening component. Only applies to hover and focus events.

attributes.name: eager
attributes.description: Forces the component's content to render when it mounts. This is useful if you have content that will not be rendered in the DOM that you want crawled for SEO.

attributes.name: locationStrategy
attributes.description: A function used to specifies how the component should position relative to its activator.

attributes.name: origin
attributes.description: Sets the transition origin on the element. You can find more information on the MDN documentation [for transition origin](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/transform-origin).

attributes.name: offset
attributes.description: Increases distance from the target. When passed as a pair of numbers, the second value shifts anchor along the side and away from the target.

attributes.name: stickToTarget
attributes.description: Enables the overlay content to go off-screen when scrolling.

attributes.name: viewportMargin
attributes.description: Sets custom viewport margin for the overlay content

attributes.name: scrollStrategy
attributes.description: Strategy used when the component is activate and user scrolls.

attributes.name: retainFocus
attributes.description: Captures and keeps focus within the content element when using **Tab** and **Shift**+**Tab**. Recommended to be `false` when using external tools that require focus such as TinyMCE or vue-clipboard.

attributes.name: type
attributes.description: A string which is one of `month`, `week`, `day`, `4day`, `custom-weekly`, `custom-daily`, and `category`. The custom types look at the `start` and `end` dates passed to the component as opposed to the `value`.

attributes.name: modelValue
attributes.description: The v-model value of the component. If component supports the **multiple** prop, this defaults to an empty array.

attributes.name: start
attributes.description: The starting date on the calendar (inclusive) in the format of `YYYY-MM-DD`. This may be ignored depending on the `type` of the calendar.

attributes.name: end
attributes.description: The ending date on the calendar (inclusive) in the format of `YYYY-MM-DD`. This may be ignored depending on the `type` of the calendar.

attributes.name: categoryDays
attributes.description: The number of days to render in the `category` view.

attributes.name: categories
attributes.description: Specifies what categories to display in the `category` view. This controls the order of the categories as well. If the calendar uses events any categories specified in those events not specified in this value are dynamically rendered in the view unless `category-hide-dynamic` is true.

value.type:
| string
  | (string | { name: string; categoryName: string; [string]: any })[]

attributes.name: categoryText
attributes.description: If categories is a list of objects, you can use this to determine what property to print out as the category text on the calendar. You can provide a function to do some logic or just define the prop name. It's similar to item-text on v-select

value.type:
| string
  | ((
      category: string | { name: string; categoryName: string; [string]: any },
    ) => string)

attributes.name: maxDays
attributes.description: The maximum number of days to display in the custom calendar if an `end` day is not set.

attributes.name: categoryHideDynamic
attributes.description: Sets whether categories specified in an event should be hidden if it's not defined in `categories`.

attributes.name: categoryShowAll
attributes.description: Set whether the `category` view should show all defined `categories` even if there are no events for a category.

attributes.name: categoryForInvalid
attributes.description: The category to place events in that have invalid categories. A category is invalid when it is not a string. By default events without a category are not displayed until this value is specified.

attributes.name: weekdays
attributes.description: An array of weekdays to display. Does not affect the order.

attributes.name: firstDayOfWeek
attributes.description: Sets the first day of the week, starting with 0 for Sunday. (Note: not guaranteed to work when using custom date adapters.)

attributes.name: firstDayOfYear
attributes.description: Sets the day that determines the first week of the year, starting with 0 for Sunday. For ISO 8601 this should be 4. (Note: not guaranteed to work when using custom date adapters.)

attributes.name: weekdayFormat
attributes.description: Formats day of the week string that appears in the header to specified locale

attributes.name: dayFormat
attributes.description: Formats day of the month string that appears in a day to a specified locale

attributes.name: locale
attributes.description: The locale of the calendar.

attributes.name: now
attributes.description: Override the day & time which is considered now. This is in the format of `YYYY-MM-DD hh:mm:ss`. The calendar is styled according to now.

attributes.name: events
attributes.description: An array of event objects with a property for a start timestamp and optionally a name and end timestamp. If an end timestamp is not given, the value of start will be used. If no name is given, you must provide an implementation for the `event` slot.

attributes.name: eventStart
attributes.description: Set property of *event*'s start timestamp.

attributes.name: eventEnd
attributes.description: Set property of *event*'s end timestamp.

attributes.name: eventTimed
attributes.description: If Dates or milliseconds are used as the start or end timestamp of an event, this prop can be a string to a property on the event that is truthy if the event is a timed event or a function which takes the event and returns a truthy value if the event is a timed event.

attributes.name: eventCategory
attributes.description: Set property of *event*'s category. Instead of a property a function can be given which takes an event and returns the category.

attributes.name: eventHeight
attributes.description: The height of an event in pixels in the `month` view and at the top of the `day` views.

attributes.name: eventColor
attributes.description: A background color for all events or a function which accepts an event object passed to the calendar to return a color.

attributes.name: eventTextColor
attributes.description: A text color for all events or a function which accepts an event object passed to the calendar to return a color.

attributes.name: eventName
attributes.description: Set property of *event*'s displayed name, or a function which accepts an event object passed to the calendar as the first argument and a flag signalling whether the name is for a timed event (true) or an event over a day.

value.type: | string | (( event: CalendarEventParsed, timedEvent: boolean, ) => string | VNode)

attributes.name: eventOverlapThreshold
attributes.description: A value in minutes that's used to determine whether two timed events should be placed in column beside each other or should be treated as slightly overlapping events.

attributes.name: eventOverlapMode
attributes.description: One of `stack`, `column`, or a custom render function

value.type: | 'stack' | 'column' | (( events: CalendarEventParsed[], firstWeekday: number, overlapThreshold: number, ) => ( day: CalendarDaySlotScope, dayEvents: CalendarEventParsed[], timed: boolean, reset: boolean, ) => CalendarEventVisual[])

attributes.description: Whether the more 'button' is displayed on a calendar with too many events in a given day. It will say something like '5 more' and when clicked generates a `click:more` event.

attributes.name: eventMoreText
attributes.description: The text to display in the more 'button' given the number of hidden events.

attributes.description: Applies the `v-ripple` directive.

attributes.name: alwaysFilter
attributes.description: When enabled, dropdown list will always show items matching non-empty value within the field. Recommended when the list is meant to show suggestions rather than options to choose from. For optimal UX, should be combined with `:menu-icon="false"` and `hide-selected`.

attributes.name: autoSelectFirst
attributes.description: When searching, will always highlight the first option and select it on blur. `exact` will only highlight and select exact matches.

attributes.name: clearOnSelect
attributes.description: Reset the search text when a selection is made while using the **multiple** prop.

attributes.name: filterMode
attributes.description:
Controls how the results of `customFilter` and `customKeyFilter` are combined. All modes only apply `customFilter` to columns not specified in `customKeyFilter`.

- **some**: There is at least one match from either the custom filter or the custom key filter.
- **every**: All columns match either the custom filter or the custom key filter.
- **union**: There is at least one match from the custom filter, or all columns match the custom key filters.
- **intersection**: There is at least one match from the custom filter, and all columns match the custom key filters.

attributes.name: noFilter
attributes.description: Disables all item filtering.

attributes.name: customFilter
attributes.description: Function used to filter items, called for each filterable key on each item in the list. The first argument is the filterable value from the item, the second is the search term, and the third is the internal item object. The function should return true if the item should be included in the filtered list, or the index of the match in the value if it should be included with the result highlighted.

attributes.name: customKeyFilter
attributes.description: Function used on specific keys within the item object. `customFilter` is skipped for columns with `customKeyFilter` specified.

attributes.name: filterKeys
attributes.description: Array of specific keys to filter on the item.

attributes.name: chips
attributes.description: Changes display of selections to chips.

attributes.name: closableChips

attributes.name: hideNoData
attributes.description: Hides the menu when there are no options to show.  Useful for preventing the menu from opening before results are fetched asynchronously.  Also has the effect of opening the menu when the `items` array changes if not already open.

attributes.name: hideSelected
attributes.description: Do not display in the select menu items that are already selected.

attributes.name: itemValue
attributes.description: Property on supplied `items` that contains its value.

attributes.name: itemChildren

attributes.description:
Controls how the results of `customFilter` and `customKeyFilter` are combined. All modes only apply `customFilter` to columns not specified in `customKeyFilter`.

- **some**: There is at least one match from either the custom filter or the custom key filter.
- **every**: All columns match either the custom filter or the custom key filter.
- **union**: There is at least one match from the custom filter, or all columns match the custom key filters.
- **intersection**: There is at least one match from the custom filter, and all columns match the custom key filters.

attributes.name: filterMode
attributes.description:
Controls how the results of `customFilter` and `customKeyFilter` are combined. All modes only apply `customFilter` to columns not specified in `customKeyFilter`.

- **some**: There is at least one match from either the custom filter or the custom key filter.
- **every**: All columns match either the custom filter or the custom key filter.
- **union**: There is at least one match from the custom filter, or all columns match the custom key filters.
- **intersection**: There is at least one match from the custom filter, and all columns match the custom key filters.

attributes.name: noFilter
attributes.description: Disables all item filtering.

attributes.name: customFilter
attributes.description: Function used to filter items, called for each filterable key on each item in the list. The first argument is the filterable value from the item, the second is the search term, and the third is the internal item object. The function should return true if the item should be included in the filtered list, or the index of the match in the value if it should be included with the result highlighted.

attributes.name: keys
attributes.description:
String representing keyboard shortcuts to display. Supports multiple formats:
- **Single keys:** `"k"`, `"enter"`, `"escape"`
- **Key combinations:** `"ctrl+k"`, `"meta+shift+p"`, `"alt+arrowup"`
- **Sequential actions:** `"ctrl+k-then-p"` (use dash for 'then' relationships)
- **Multiple shortcuts:** `"ctrl+k meta+p"` (space-separated for alternative shortcuts)

Supports platform-aware key names like `meta` (becomes Cmd on Mac, Ctrl on PC) and `alt` (becomes Option on Mac).

attributes.name: variant
attributes.description:
Controls the visual style and presentation of the hotkey component. Supports standard Vuetify variants plus a special contained variant:

**Standard Variants** (apply styling to individual key elements):
- **elevated (default):** Raised appearance with shadow, good for standalone hotkey displays
- **flat:** Solid background without shadow, clean and minimal
- **tonal:** Subtle tinted background without border, balances visibility with restraint
- **outlined:** Border-only styling without elevation, lightweight and unobtrusive
- **text:** Minimal styling with text color emphasis only, blends with content
- **plain:** No background or border, most subtle option

**Special Variant** (different visual structure):
- **contained:** Follows MDN's nested `<kbd>` pattern - wraps all keys in a single styled container with unstyled nested elements. Creates a cohesive visual unit that clearly groups related keys together. Cannot be combined with standard variants. Ideal for complex key combinations where you want to show the entire sequence as one unit.

attributes.name: inline
attributes.description: Optimizes the component for seamless integration within text content and documentation. Applies compact styling with baseline alignment, constrained height (1lh), and responsive typography that inherits from parent text. Ideal for help documentation, tooltips, and instructional content. When using multiple inline hotkeys in the same paragraph, increase line-height to prevent visual overlap on text wrapping.

attributes.name: suffix
attributes.description: Text to display after the hotkey.

attributes.name: displayMode
attributes.description:
Controls how keyboard keys are visually represented. Affects the entire component's appearance:
- **icon:** Uses SVG icons for keys when appropriate (default)
- **symbol:** Uses Unicode symbols (, , , ) - Allows you to manage presentation of modifier keys with fonts
- **text:** Uses full text labels (Command, Control, Shift, Alt) - most accessible and descriptive

attributes.name: keyMap
platform
attributes.description:
Controls platform-specific rendering behavior for keyboard shortcuts. Accepts three values:
- **`'auto'` (default):** Automatically detects the user's platform based on user agent and renders appropriately
- **`'mac'`:** Forces Mac-style rendering (Command symbols, icons, Option key, etc.)
- **`'pc'`:** Forces PC-style rendering (Ctrl text, Alt key, etc.)

This is particularly useful for:
- **Cross-platform testing:** Verify how shortcuts appear on different platforms
- **Design consistency:** Ensure specific platform rendering in demos and prototypes
- **Development workflow:** Test platform-specific behaviors without switching devices
- **Documentation:** Show platform-specific examples in help content

attributes.name: activeStrategy
attributes.description:
Affects how items with children behave when activated. If not specified, the **single-independent** strategy will be used.
- **leaf:** Only leaf nodes (items without children) can be activated.
- **single-leaf:** Similar as **leaf**, but only a single item can be activated at a time.
- **independent:** All nodes can be activated whether they have children or not.
- **single-independent:** Similar as **independent**, but only a single item can be activated at a time.

attributes.name: selectStrategy
attributes.description:
Affects how items with children behave when selected.
- **leaf:** Only leaf nodes (items without children) can be selected.
- **independent:** All nodes can be selected whether they have children or not.
- **classic:** Selecting a parent node will cause all children to be selected, parent nodes will be displayed as selected if all their descendants are selected. Only leaf nodes will be added to the model.
- **trunk**: Same as classic but if all of a node's children are selected then only that node will be added to the model.

attributes.name: openStrategy
attributes.description:
Affects how items with children behave when expanded.
- **multiple:** Any number of groups can be open at once.
- **single:** Only one group at each level can be open, opening a group will cause others to close.
- **list:** Multiple, but all other groups will close when an item is selected.

attributes.description: Closes the overlay content when the browser's back button is pressed or `$router.back()` is called, cancelling the original navigation. `persistent` overlays will cancel navigation and animate as if they were clicked outside instead of closing.

attributes.description: Applies a custom class to the detached element. This is useful because the content is moved to the beginning of the `v-app` component (unless the **attach** prop is provided) and is not targetable by classes passed directly on the component.

attributes.name: noClickAnimation

attributes.name: attach
attributes.description: Specifies which DOM element the overlay content should teleport to. Can be a direct element reference, querySelector string, or `true` to disable teleporting. Uses `body` by default. Generally not recommended except as a last resort: the default positioning algorithm should handle most scenarios better than is possible without teleporting, and you may have unexpected behavior if the menu ends up as child of its activator.

attributes.name: showArrows
attributes.description: Change when the overflow arrow indicators are shown. By **default**, arrows *always* display on Desktop when the container is overflowing. When the container overflows on mobile, arrows are not shown by default. A **show-arrows** value of `true` allows these arrows to show on Mobile if the container overflowing. A value of `desktop` *always* displays arrows on Desktop while a value of `mobile` always displays arrows on Mobile. A value of `always` always displays arrows on Desktop *and* Mobile. Use **never** to turn arrows off. Find more information on how to customize breakpoint thresholds on the [breakpoints page](/customizing/breakpoints).

attributes.name: closeOnBack
attributes.description: Closes the overlay content when the browser's back button is pressed or `$router.back()` is called, cancelling the original navigation. `persistent` overlays will cancel navigation and animate as if they were clicked outside instead of closing.

attributes.name: contained
attributes.description: Limits the size of the component and scrim to its offset parent. Implies `absolute` and `attach`. (Note: The parent element must have position: relative.).

attributes.name: contentClass
attributes.description: Applies a custom class to the detached element. This is useful because the content is moved to the beginning of the `v-app` component (unless the **attach** prop is provided) and is not targetable by classes passed directly on the component.

attributes.description: Apply custom properties to the content.

attributes.description: Sets the opacity of the scrim element. Only applies if `scrim` is enabled.

attributes.name: zIndex
attributes.description: The z-index used for the component.

attributes.name: target
attributes.description: For locationStrategy="connected", specify an element or array of x,y coordinates that the overlay should position itself relative to. This will be the activator element by default.

attributes.name: activatorProps
attributes.description: Apply custom properties to the activator.

attributes.name: openOnClick
attributes.description: Activate the component when the activator is clicked.

attributes.name: openOnHover
attributes.description: Activate the component when the activator is hovered.

attributes.name: openOnFocus
attributes.description: Activate the component when the activator is focused.

attributes.name: closeOnContentClick
attributes.description: Closes component when you click on its content.

attributes.name: closeDelay
attributes.description: Milliseconds to wait before closing component. Only applies to hover and focus events.

attributes.name: openDelay
attributes.description: Milliseconds to wait before opening component. Only applies to hover and focus events.

attributes.name: eager
attributes.description: Forces the component's content to render when it mounts. This is useful if you have content that will not be rendered in the DOM that you want crawled for SEO.

attributes.name: locationStrategy
attributes.description: A function used to specifies how the component should position relative to its activator.

attributes.name: origin
attributes.description: Sets the transition origin on the element. You can find more information on the MDN documentation [for transition origin](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/transform-origin).

attributes.name: offset
attributes.description: Increases distance from the target. When passed as a pair of numbers, the second value shifts anchor along the side and away from the target.

attributes.name: attach
attributes.description: Specifies which DOM element the overlay content should teleport to. Can be a direct element reference, querySelector string, or `true` to disable teleporting. Uses `body` by default.

attributes.name: vertical

attributes.name: openOnClick
attributes.description: When `true` will cause nodes to be opened by clicking anywhere on it, instead of only opening by clicking on expand icon. When using this prop with `activatable` you will be unable to mark nodes with children as active.

attributes.description: Hide the expand icon and loading indicator next to each item title.

attributes.name: filterMode
attributes.description:
Controls how the results of `customFilter` and `customKeyFilter` are combined. All modes only apply `customFilter` to columns not specified in `customKeyFilter`.

- **some**: There is at least one match from either the custom filter or the custom key filter.
- **every**: All columns match either the custom filter or the custom key filter.
- **union**: There is at least one match from the custom filter, or all columns match the custom key filters.
- **intersection**: There is at least one match from the custom filter, and all columns match the custom key filters.

attributes.name: noFilter
attributes.description: Disables all item filtering.

attributes.name: customFilter
attributes.description: Function used to filter items, called for each filterable key on each item in the list. The first argument is the filterable value from the item, the second is the search term, and the third is the internal item object. The function should return true if the item should be included in the filtered list, or the index of the match in the value if it should be included with the result highlighted.

attributes.name: customKeyFilter
attributes.description: Function used on specific keys within the item object. `customFilter` is skipped for columns with `customKeyFilter` specified.

attributes.name: filterKeys
attributes.description: Array of specific keys to filter on the item.

attributes.name: hideNoData
attributes.description: Hides the menu when there are no options to show.  Useful for preventing the menu from opening before results are fetched asynchronously.  Also has the effect of opening the menu when the `items` array changes if not already open.

attributes.name: filterable
attributes.description: **FOR INTERNAL USE ONLY** Prevents list item selection using [space] key and pass it back to the text input. Used internally for VAutocomplete and VCombobox.

attributes.name: expandIcon

attributes.name: collapseIcon
attributes.description: Icon to display when the list item is expanded.

attributes.name: prependGap
attributes.description: Sets the horizontal spacing between prepend slot and the main content within list item. Also affects indent to ensure expected alignment of group children.

attributes.name: indent
attributes.description: Overrides the indent size for nested groups.

attributes.name: activatable
attributes.description: Allows user to mark a node as active by clicking on it.

attributes.name: selectable
attributes.description: Will render a checkbox next to each node allowing them to be selected. Additionally, the **[openOnClick](/api/v-treeview/#props-open-on-click)** property will be applied internally.

attributes.name: opened
attributes.description: An array containing the values of currently opened groups. Can be two-way bound with `v-model:opened`.

attributes.name: itemsRegistration
attributes.description: When set to 'props', skips rendering collapsed items/nodes (for significant performance gains).

attributes.name: activeStrategy
attributes.description:
Affects how items with children behave when activated. If not specified, the **single-independent** strategy will be used.
- **leaf:** Only leaf nodes (items without children) can be activated.
- **single-leaf:** Similar as **leaf**, but only a single item can be activated at a time.
- **independent:** All nodes can be activated whether they have children or not.
- **single-independent:** Similar as **independent**, but only a single item can be activated at a time.

attributes.name: selectStrategy
attributes.description:
Affects how items with children behave when selected.
- **leaf:** Only leaf nodes (items without children) can be selected.
- **independent:** All nodes can be selected whether they have children or not.
- **classic:** Selecting a parent node will cause all children to be selected, parent nodes will be displayed as selected if all their descendants are selected. Only leaf nodes will be added to the model.
- **trunk**: Same as classic but if all of a node's children are selected then only that node will be added to the model.
